06/08/2004
THESSALONIKI, Greece -- The Museum of Sports in Thessaloniki was officially opened on Thursday (5 August) in a ceremony attended by International Olympic Committee President Jacques Rogge and Greek Olympic Committee President Lambis Nikolaou.
Government and local officials were on hand, as were several prominent Greek sports figures.
The museum includes over 2,000 exhibits.
Asked to comment on the upcoming Athens Olympics, Rogge said he is confident of their success.
(ANA, MPA - 05/08/04)
